headline: Key Ohio Dems ask party to stay neutral in governor primary
author: Associated Press
sentences: COLUMBUS— Some high-profile Democrats in Ohio are urging party leaders to remain neutral in the competitive primary between gubernatorial candidates Nan Whaley and John Cranley, as the party works to support the pick best capable of leading its ticket to long-sought wins this fall.
The push comes as screeners from the Ohio Democratic Party’s Executive Committee are set to meet Tuesday to decide who to recommend.
